Program: The History Hour
Title: Operation Lifeline: Canada's Refugee Revolution
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p05465lf
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 4 Jun 2017
How private citizens in Canada sponsored Vietnamese boat-people. Plus the first ever charity rock concert for Chernobyl, the actor who stared in a Hitchcock murder movie, America's first ever female rabbi and Mr Sanitation brings clean toilets in India. Photo: A Vietnamese boat crowded with refugees runs aground on the Malaysian coast. 1979 (BBC) Show less